# Trivy waivers — ollama image only (wired to the ollama scan step in
# .github/workflows/ci.yml via the `trivyignores:` input; NOT applied to the
# neo4j or pgvector scans, which stay strict).
#
# Context (Issue #4): the upstream ollama/ollama:0.22.1 pin went CVE-stale once
# Issue #2/#4 unmasked the security job — the Trivy step flagged HIGH/CRITICAL
# Go `stdlib` CVEs (crypto/tls, net/http2, net/url, archive/*) compiled into the
# ollama server binary, plus github.com/buger/jsonparser. Bumped to 0.24.0 (the
# freshest aged stable, 7 days old) to minimise residual, but these are
# *compile-time toolchain* CVEs: no ollama tag fixes them — only an upstream
# rebuild on a patched Go (1.25.10 / 1.26.3) does. So they are waived here, the
# same class as the neo4j netty waiver (a dependency the image bundles itself).
#
# Reachability for THIS deployment (spec §6.7 accept-with-justification): ollama
# is bound to 127.0.0.1, single trusted user, and the Story Forge backend is its
# only client — there is no untrusted network peer. The stdlib CVEs are
# predominantly DoS (parsing resource-exhaustion in HTTP/2, URL, archive, mail
# code) which a single trusted caller would only inflict on itself; the
# crypto/tls and crypto/x509 cert-validation issues apply to ollama's *outbound*
# TLS (to Ollama Cloud) and would require an active MITM of that connection.
#
# All waivers across images are also indexed in infra/trivy/WAIVERS.md (the
# review register: fixed-in versions + drop conditions, checked periodically).
#
# Revisit: every ollama tag bump. Drop these entries the moment a rebuilt ollama
# image ships on a patched Go toolchain (re-scan should pass without the waiver).
#
# The 0.24.0 set (12 HIGH, 0 CRITICAL) was enumerated by the CI Trivy run on
# commit 282e3da (local Trivy was unavailable this session). The bump from
# 0.22.1 already dropped the CRITICAL crypto/tls resumption CVE and 6 others.

# ─────────────────────── OS package (Ubuntu base) ───────────────────────
# CVE-2026-45447 — openssl/libssl3t64 (HIGH): heap use-after-free in PKCS7_verify()
# when a PKCS#7 SignedData carries an empty digestAlgorithms SET (OpenSSL frees a
# caller-owned BIO; a later use crashes — potential RCE). Reachable ONLY by code
# that verifies attacker-supplied PKCS#7 / S-MIME messages via OpenSSL's PKCS7 API;
# ollama serves a JSON inference API and does no PKCS#7/S-MIME verification, bound
# to 127.0.0.1 with the trusted local backend as its only client. Fixed in Ubuntu
# openssl 3.0.13-0ubuntu3.11 (upstream 3.5.7); not yet in an ollama rebuild.
# Disclosed 2026-06-10; same CVE waived on neo4j/pgvector. (Verified vs OpenSSL advisory.)
CVE-2026-45447

# ─────────────── Bundled dependency: github.com/buger/jsonparser ───────────────
# CVE-2026-32285 — DoS via crafted JSON triggering a panic / unbounded work in
# the parser. Fixed in jsonparser 1.1.2. Reached only by JSON the trusted local
# backend sends to ollama; a single trusted caller would only affect itself.
CVE-2026-32285

# ──────────────────── Bundled: Go stdlib (ollama binary) ───────────────────────
# Compiled into the ollama server binary; fixable only by an upstream rebuild on
# a patched Go toolchain (versions noted per CVE). Predominantly DoS in parsing
# code a single trusted localhost caller would only inflict on itself; the two
# crypto/x509 cert-validation issues affect ollama's *outbound* TLS and need an
# active MITM to exploit.

# CVE-2026-25679 — net/url: insufficient host/authority component validation in
# url.Parse (accepts certain invalid URLs). Parsing DoS-class on URLs from a trusted
# local caller only. Fixed Go 1.25.8 / 1.26.1.
CVE-2026-25679
# CVE-2026-27137 — crypto/x509: incorrect enforcement of email constraints in cert
# validation (validation-correctness, not RCE). Fixed Go 1.26.1.
CVE-2026-27137
# CVE-2026-32280 — crypto/x509: DoS in certificate-chain building. Fixed Go 1.25.9 / 1.26.2.
CVE-2026-32280
# CVE-2026-32281 — crypto/x509: DoS via inefficient chain validation. Fixed Go 1.25.9 / 1.26.2.
CVE-2026-32281
# CVE-2026-32283 — crypto/tls: DoS via multiple TLS 1.3 key updates. Fixed Go 1.25.9 / 1.26.2.
CVE-2026-32283
# CVE-2026-33810 — crypto/x509: certificate-validation issue (correctness). Fixed Go 1.26.2.
CVE-2026-33810
# CVE-2026-33811 — net (cgo resolver): long CNAME in LookupCNAME triggers a double-free
# of C memory + crash (higher severity than the earlier "DoS" description suggested).
# Reachable only via outbound DNS in cgo mode; trusted DNS source. Fixed Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-33811
# CVE-2026-33814 — net/http2: infinite loop on crafted SETTINGS frames (DoS). Fixed Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-33814
# CVE-2026-39820 — net/mail: DoS via crafted ParseAddress / ParseAddressList input. Fixed Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-39820
# CVE-2026-39836 — net: panic in Dial / LookupPort on NUL byte (Windows). Fixed Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-39836
# CVE-2026-42499 — net/mail: DoS via consumePhrase on pathological input. Fixed Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-42499

# ─── Third wave (disclosed 2026-05-26 → 2026-05-27, same Go-stdlib backlog) ───
# Sequential-Trivy unmask: PR #23's pgvector wave-3 waiver let Trivy reach this
# scan, which then flagged the *same three* Go-stdlib CVEs in the compiled
# ollama server binary (built on Go 1.26.0, older than the patched 1.25.10/
# 1.26.3). Fold matches the precedent from PR #6 (Issue #4) where fixing
# pgvector unmasked ollama and both landed together. Tracked under Issue #22
# (the build-our-own-image evaluation is pgvector-scoped; ollama remains on
# upstream).

# CVE-2026-39823 — html/template (HIGH): URLs are not correctly escaped inside
# `<meta>` tag content attributes; ASCII whitespace around `=` bypasses the
# escaper, enabling XSS. ollama is a JSON HTTP API server — it renders no HTML
# templates, so the vulnerable code path is unreachable.
CVE-2026-39823
# CVE-2026-39825 — net/http/httputil (HIGH): ReverseProxy forwards query
# parameters not visible to the configured Rewrite function once ParseQuery's
# parameter limit is exceeded. ollama is an HTTP *server*, not a reverse
# proxy; httputil.ReverseProxy is not in its request path.
CVE-2026-39825
# CVE-2026-39826 — html/template (HIGH): incorrect data escaping when a
# `<script>` tag has an empty or whitespace-only `type` attribute. ollama
# returns JSON and renders no HTML templates, so the vulnerable code path is
# unreachable.
CVE-2026-39826
# CVE-2026-42504 — mime (HIGH): quadratic complexity in WordDecoder.DecodeHeader
# (CWE-407) — a crafted MIME header with many invalid encoded-words consumes
# excessive CPU (DoS). Reachable only by feeding crafted MIME headers; ollama is
# bound to 127.0.0.1 with the Story Forge backend as its only (trusted) client,
# so there is no untrusted peer to inflict the DoS. (GO-2026-5038.)
CVE-2026-42504
# CVE-2026-27145 — crypto/x509 (HIGH): `(*x509.Certificate).VerifyHostname` hostname
# matching could be incorrect. Fixed Go 1.25.11 / 1.26.4. Applies to ollama's
# *outbound* TLS (to Ollama Cloud) and needs an active MITM of that connection to
# exploit; cert-validation correctness, not RCE. (Surfaced by the Trivy DB 2026-06-23;
# pre-empted here — same sub-1.25.11 Go that waved CVE-2026-42504 in this binary.)
CVE-2026-27145

# ─── Wave 6: golang.org/x/crypto + golang.org/x/net modules (surfaced by the
#     Trivy DB 2026-06-23; unmasked once the stdlib CVE-2026-27145 above cleared,
#     since the security job scans sequentially) ───
#
# These are NOT Go stdlib — they are the compiled-in `golang.org/x/crypto`
# (v0.43.0, fixed 0.52.0) and `golang.org/x/net` (v0.46.0, fixed 0.55.0) modules in
# the ollama server binary. Only an upstream ollama rebuild on the patched modules
# clears them; no ollama tag we pin fixes a compiled-in dependency.
#
# Reachability — ollama is 127.0.0.1-bound, single trusted user, the Story Forge
# backend is the only client:
#
# golang.org/x/crypto/ssh (fixed 0.52.0) — ollama runs no SSH server and opens no
# SSH client connection in the inference path, so this whole package is compiled-in
# but unreachable. Each entry is an SSH-only issue:
# CVE-2026-39827 — ssh: authenticated client repeatedly opening channels → DoS.
CVE-2026-39827
# CVE-2026-39828 — ssh: denial of service.
CVE-2026-39828
# CVE-2026-39829 — ssh: denial of service.
CVE-2026-39829
# CVE-2026-39830 — ssh: denial of service.
CVE-2026-39830
# CVE-2026-39835 — ssh: servers using CertChecker as a public-key callback. ollama
# runs no SSH server.
CVE-2026-39835
# CVE-2026-42508 — ssh/knownhosts: revocation bypass. ollama does no SSH host-key
# checking.
CVE-2026-42508
# CVE-2026-46595 — ssh: denial of service.
CVE-2026-46595
# CVE-2026-46597 — ssh: an incorrectly placed bytes→int cast (parsing). ollama runs
# no SSH.
CVE-2026-46597
#
# golang.org/x/net (fixed 0.55.0):
# CVE-2026-25680 — net/html: parsing arbitrary HTML consumes excessive CPU (DoS).
# ollama returns JSON and parses/renders no HTML, so the path is unreachable.
CVE-2026-25680
# CVE-2026-25681 — net/html: arbitrary HTML rendered via Render. Unreachable (no HTML).
CVE-2026-25681
# CVE-2026-27136 — net/html: arbitrary HTML rendered via Render. Unreachable (no HTML).
CVE-2026-27136
# CVE-2026-39821 — net/idna: privilege escalation via incorrect Punycode label
# processing. Reachable only on ollama's *outbound* TLS to a model registry and only
# with an attacker-controlled internationalized hostname — which the single trusted
# local user supplies; not reachable by any untrusted peer here.
CVE-2026-39821
# CVE-2026-42502 — net/html: arbitrary HTML rendered via Render. Unreachable (no HTML).
CVE-2026-42502
# CVE-2026-42506 — net/html: arbitrary HTML rendered via Render. Unreachable (no HTML).
CVE-2026-42506
